  "text": "## Retry with Exponential Backoff Patterns Across Go Repositories\n\n### Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\nKubernetes implements exponential backoff through multiple layered components:\n\n**Core Implementation:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/backoff.go`: Contains the primary `ExponentialBackoff(backoff Backoff, condition ConditionFunc)` function which implements the wait-retry pattern. It decays through backoff.Steps with exponentially increasing wait durations using `backoff.Step()`. Also provides `ExponentialBackoffWithContext()` for context-aware cancellation.\n- `pkg/util/goroutinemap/exponentialbackoff/exponential_backoff.go`: Defines the `ExponentialBackoff` struct with `SafeToRetry()`, `Update()`, and `NewExponentialBackoffError()` methods. Uses initial duration of 500ms, doubling up to 2m2s max.\n\n**Client Retry Wrapper:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/retry/util.go`: The `OnError()` function wraps `wait.ExponentialBackoff()` to retry functions on specific retriable errors using the conflict-safe `DefaultRetry` backoff config (5 steps, 1s initial, 1.5x factor).\n\n**Webhook Integration:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/webhook.go`: Implements `WithExponentialBackoff()` function for webhook retry (up to 5 attempts). Provides `DefaultRetryBackoffWithInitialDelay()` for custom webhook backoff configuration.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/authenticator/token/webhook/webhook.go`: Uses `DefaultRetryBackoff()` for token review webhook retries.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go`: Creates audit webhook backend with configurable `retryBackoff`.\n\n**Component Usage:**\n- `pkg/util/goroutinemap/goroutinemap.go`: GoRoutineMap uses exponentialbackoff.ExponentialBackoff for operation-level backoff tracking.\n- `pkg/volume/util/nestedpendingoperations/nestedpendingoperations.go`: NestedPendingOperations uses exponentialbackoff.ExponentialBackoff in operation struct.\n- `test/utils/create_resources.go`: Test helper `RetryWithExponentialBackOff()` uses wait.ExponentialBackoff with fixed parameters (100ms, 3x factor, 0 jitter, 6 steps).\n- `pkg/kubelet/watchdog/watchdog_linux.go`: Uses `wait.ExponentialBackoffWithContext()` for watchdog systemd notification.\n- `pkg/kubelet/nodeshutdown/nodeshutdown_manager_linux.go`: Uses `wait.ExponentialBackoff()` to reload login configuration.\n- `pkg/volume/csi/csi_plugin.go`: CSI plugin initialization uses exponential backoff (30ms initial, 1.5x factor).\n\n**Rate Limiting:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/default_rate_limiters.go`: Defines `TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter` for work queue rate limiting with exponential backoff.\n\n### Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n\nGrafana uses multiple exponential backoff implementations across different services:\n\n**Git Repository Retry:**\n- `apps/provisioning/pkg/repository/git/repository.go`: Imports `github.com/grafana/nanogit/retry` (external library) and uses `retry.ExponentialBackoffRetrier` via `defaultGitRetrier()` with 8 max attempts (1 initial + 7 retries), 100ms initial delay, capped at 5 seconds. Integrates via `ensureRetryContext()` and `retry.FromContext()`/`retry.ToContext()`.\n\n**Alert Scheduling:**\n- `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/retry.go`: Implements `newExponentialBackoffRetryer()` wrapping `backoff.BackOff` from cenkalti/backoff library with max retries, initial/max delays, and randomization factor.\n- `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/recording_rule.go`: Uses the exponential backoff retrier for recording rule execution.\n\n**Resource Provisioning:**\n- `pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/resources/retry_client.go`: Wraps dynamic.ResourceInterface with `retryWithBackoff()` using Kubernetes' `wait.ExponentialBackoff` (100ms initial, 2x factor, 0.1 jitter, 8 steps, 5s cap). Test at line 431 validates exponential backoff calculation.\n\n**Generic Retry Helper:**\n- `pkg/util/retryer/retryer.go`: Provides `Retry()` function with manual exponential backoff calculation: `delay := minDelay * time.Duration(1<<attempt)`. Supports maxRetries and delay capping.\n\n**gRPC Interceptors:**\n- `pkg/storage/unified/client_retry.go`: Uses `grpc_retry.BackoffExponentialWithJitter()` with configurable backoff and jitter (1s backoff, 0.1-0.5 jitter) for unary client calls.\n- `pkg/server/ring.go`: Defines `connectionBackoffOptions()` using gRPC's `grpc.ConnectParams` with 100ms base delay for reconnection backoff.\n- `pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go`: Similar gRPC retry with `grpc_retry.BackoffExponentialWithJitter()`.\n- `pkg/services/apiserver/options/storage.go`: gRPC retry configuration for unified storage.\n\n**Database Operations:**\n- `pkg/services/sqlstore/session.go`: Uses `pkg/util/retryer/retryer.Retry()` for database query retries with 10ms min and 1s max delay.\n- `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrator/sqlite_dialect.go`: SQLite uses dskit `backoff.New()` with 100ms-1s range and 5 max retries for handling locked database tables.\n\n**Other Services:**\n- `apps/advisor/pkg/app/checktyperegisterer/checktyperegisterer.go`: Manual exponential backoff: `delay := retryDelay * time.Duration(1<<attempt)`.\n\n### Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n\nPrometheus implements exponential backoff for remote write operations:\n\n**Core Remote Write Backoff:**\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go`: Central function `sendWriteRequestWithBackoff()` implements the main exponential backoff loop for remote write. Tracks MinBackoff and MaxBackoff from configuration. Doubles backoff on each retry (line 2081: `backoff = min(sleepDuration*2, t.cfg.MaxBackoff)`). Respects Retry-After headers when present. Also contains `sendSamplesWithBackoff()`, `sendV2SamplesWithBackoff()`, and `sendMetadataWithBackoff()` wrapper functions that call into the core backoff logic.\n\n**Configuration:**\n- `config/config.go`: Defines `QueueConfig` struct with `MinBackoff` (default 30ms) and `MaxBackoff` (default 5s) fields. `RemoteWriteConfig` uses these for retry backoff on recoverable errors.\n\n**Client Implementation:**\n- `storage/remote/client.go`: Remote write client uses the QueueManager's backoff infrastructure.\n\n**Testing:**\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager_test.go`: Test cases like `TestSendSamplesWithBackoffWithSampleAgeLimit()` validate the exponential backoff behavior with configurable MinBackoff and MaxBackoff (typically 100ms for tests).\n\n**Write Handlers:**\n- `storage/remote/write.go`: WriteStorage manages multiple queue managers with exponential backoff.\n- `storage/remote/write_handler.go`: Handles incoming remote write requests.\n\n## Cross-Repository Pattern Summary\n\nAll three repositories implement exponential backoff with the pattern: initial_delay → initial_delay*2 → initial_delay*4 → ... up to max_delay. Key differences:\n\n- **Kubernetes**: Native implementation via `wait.Backoff` struct with configurable Duration, Factor, Steps, Jitter, and Cap.\n- **Grafana**: Hybrid approach using external libraries (nanogit's retry, cenkalti/backoff) plus Kubernetes' wait package for provisioning, with additional manual calculation for database retries.\n- **Prometheus**: Configuration-driven with MinBackoff/MaxBackoff parameters, doubling on each retry with Retry-After header support.\n\nAll implement context cancellation, recover from transient errors only, and cap maximum wait durations."
